d 'MIXI01': module providing econometric methods for systems mixing I(0) and I(1) variables
d
d	mixi01 is a comprehensive Stata package for estimation and
d inference in time series    systems that contain a mixture of
d I(1) (nonstationary, unit-root) and I(0) (stationary)   
d variables.  Higher orders of integration (I(2) and above) are out
d of scope; series that    are I(2) should be first-differenced to
d I(1) before being used as inputs.  The package    implements the
d fully modified (FM) estimation framework of Phillips (1995) and
d Kitamura    and Phillips (1997), the structural VAR methodology
d of Fisher, Huh and Pagan (2016) for	 systems with P0/T0/P1/T1
d shock classifications, and the mixed VECM of Chen (2022).   
d Standard cointegration methods typically require that all
d variables in a system share the    same order of integration.  In
d practice, macroeconomic systems routinely mix trending and   
d stationary variables — output, prices and interest rates, for
d example.  mixi01 provides a	 unified framework where the
d researcher does not need to pretest variables for unit roots,   
d determine the dimension of the cointegration space, or separate
d I(1) from I(0) regressors    before estimation. 
d
d KW: order of integration
d KW: statonarity
d KW: nonstationary
d
d Requires: Stata version 14 
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260521
d
d Author:   Merwan Roudane, NA
d Support: email  merwanroudane920@@gmail.com
d
f mixi01.ado
